Package fr.ens.biologie.codeGeneration

Class MethodGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.ens.biologie.codeGeneration.MethodGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JavaCode
    public class MethodGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
implements JavaCode

    A simple method code generator for java classes. It does not handle exceptions, nor annotations, and provides only limited support for generic types.

    Usage:

    1. Get an instance of ClassGenerator. If it has a superclass or implements interfaces, it will generate instances of MethodGenerator for every abstract method found in the superclass / interfaces.
    2. Get the method generator you want to work with ClassGenerator.getMethod(...) or ClassGenerator.getMethods().
    3. Update the method generator as you want, populating it with statements etc.
    4. When you call asText(...) on your ClassGenerator, it will call this class asText(...) method so that all the edits you made in your method generator will be reflected in the generated code. Basically, you should never need to call MethodGenerator.asText(...) directly - unless you want to generate the code of a single method floating outside of a class.
    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 19 d√©c. 2014
